# The image only needs the two prebuilt linux release binaries. Ignore the whole
# repo, then re-include just those, so the build context stays tiny even when the
# context is the repo root (excludes .git, node_modules, .claude, web/, dist/,
# testdata/, docs-site/, etc.). The Dockerfile is read out-of-band, not via context.
*
!costroid-linux-amd64
!costroid-linux-arm64
